~ governor_first

Governor: A stranger who restores the Statue Plaza on the way into the city. Unusual.
Governor: The guards told me what you did out there. Well done.
Governor: But I doubt you crossed the desert just to move statues. What brings you to Arenthis?
Player [#sprite=water/neutral]: My name is Jarn Thorian. I carry a message from King Aldric of Valdenmoor.
Player [#sprite=water/neutral]: The monsters are spreading beyond the desert and other city as well.
Player [#sprite=water/neutral]: King Aldric believes something is driving them. No kingdom can stop this alone.
Player [#sprite=water/neutral]: He asks for an alliance.
Governor: Three days ago sand demons hit our eastern gate. We lost good soldiers that night.
Governor: If they are pushing beyond the desert now then your king is right to be worried.
Governor: Arenthis will stand with Valdenmoor. You have my word.
Governor: Rest here. Speak to the people. When you are ready to move on come back to me.
=> END

~ governor_after

Governor: The alliance stands. Travel safe, Jarn Thorian.
=> END
